3. OPENSEARCH CLIENT WRAPPER
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 - ensureIndex(indexName, settingsJson)  : PUT index with raw JSON; idempotent (ignores resource_already_exists_exception)
 - bulkIndex(indexName, documents)       : BulkResult(errors)
 - search(indexName, query, size)        : SearchResult(hits)
 - multiMatchSearch(indexName, queryText, fields, topK) : List<SearchHit>
 - deleteByQuery(indexName, query)       : POST _delete_by_query
 - getDocCount(indexName)                : count API
 - refreshIndex(indexName)               : POST _refresh (for tests)
 - healthCheck()                         : GET _cluster/health, not red

4. INDEX SCHEMAS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 - code-artifacts   : java_code_analyzer (camelCase + Java stopwords), chunk_type, content, snapshot_id, service_name, etc.
 - config-artifacts : snapshot_id, service_name, file_path, artifact_type, content
 - runtime-events   : batch_id, service_name, log_type, timestamp, template_id, message, trace_id, severity
 - anomaly-episodes : service_name, start_time, end_time, score

5. K8S / DOCKER
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 - docker-compose: opensearch 2.18.0 (single-node, security disabled), port 9200
 - ArgoCD app: opensearch, sync-wave 2, Helm chart opensearch 2.28.0, values from k8s/infrastructure/opensearch/values.yaml
 - values: 3 replicas, 8Gi heap, 100Gi PVC, security disabled, ClusterIP 9200

